A former chairman of the Plateau State chapter of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Hon. Latep Dabang, and a former Majority Leader of the Plateau State House of Assemblyk Hon. Henry Yenkwap have defected from the ruling party APC to the opposition Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in the State. Also, a former chairman of Quanpan local government area, Hon. Isaac Kwalu, and a former member of the Plateau State House of Assembly, Hon. Nanpon Tom and their supporters were recieved by the PDP during the Langtang Mega Rally 2022 tagged the ‘Great Movement’. Dabang and Yenkwap also said they have moved to the PDP along with their numerous supporters. Details later…